    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce lessons on \"modern life\" as part of the national curriculum ",
        "additional_details": "An example would from myself. Leaving Sixth Form I went straight into a full time job. With no knowledge apart from what my parents told me on \"Adult Life\". The first time I saw my first pay check, I was confused as to why some of my money was going toward \"NI\" and as a young adult I didn't quite understand. But with lessons on these basic but new formalities entering adulthood could help the younger generations to understand what to expect.",
        "background": "Children/young adults in secondary schools should be educated on the \"modern life\" and the real \"adult\" world. They should have basic knowledge on things like pensions, mortgages, taxes etc",
